m total / 33 headlines = 63 score</p><p class="serif lh-lg"><u>The energy level falls between: grief (75) and apathy (50)</u>. If we are not consciously aware of this psychological trick of manipulation, then we\'re letting someone else create an inversion of our reality where, in this case, grief and apathy seems to be the inevitable bi-product and the only and obvious way of describing the world which surrounds us.</p><small class="serif lh-lg">Quick note: If you\'re thinking: "I can do better than that" or "I think my score would be different", I welcome you to do the same procedure and share your results. This way we can collaborate on our shared reality through statistical/propabilisitc/deterministic/karl popperistic means. An interessting discovery I bet would be that some people would make an inversion of the score which I have presented here, which in that case would also leave us pondering and thinking until we meet again in writing! It\'s my secret hope that we could integrate this little script, or program if you will, into our minds and then run it whenever it was needed in our lives with particular interest of course on the information we consume. Or maybe pen and paper to scribble down some of the energetic states you register as you encounter information as you go about your day. This would also make it clear just how much information we are consuming is creating an (un)intended consequence of blocking us from self-contemplation from moment to moment because the river keeps flowing, the feed keeps scrolling and the tv keeps rolling. Maybe if it helps you can imagine sitting in the information river with your mouth open. Maybe we better stand up and take a deep breath of fresh air once in a while!</small>',
